$interpreted: Juan-Yun: And since the Qilin Tribe made this mess, then why don't you let us clean it up?
Toyokuni: What's this kid ranting about this time...
Juan-Yun: I said this war is Qilin business, so please, all of you, just stay out of it!
Chiyuki: Yagh!!
Toyokuni: Before everyone else wakes up...
Pang: ...Did the arbiter's orders include what to do if Juan-Yun came and tried to interfere?
Chiyuki: Ah, I'm afraid not...
Pang: Yeah, I thought as much...
Toyokuni: Juan-Yun said this is Qilin Tribe business, so maybe we shouldn't interfere.
Toyokuni: Ah, forget it. Juan-Yun's spirit wind won't last for much longer. We can wait and apprehend her once it does.
Himawari: (Juan-Yun... Damn, we were so close!)
Tindoiimu: ...Are you here to arrest me, too?
Juan-Yun: Princess...
Juan-Yun: We don't have much time, so I'm going to say this quickly.
Tindoiimu: ......
Juan-Yun: The arbiter was alerted even before you freed the hostages.
Juan-Yun: She didn't have time to gather her elite forces, so she could only ask Chiyuki to get all the contestants together.
Tindoiimu: Before I freed them...?
Juan-Yun: Someone sold you out. I don't know who.
Tindoiimu: ......
Juan-Yun: The second I caught wind of what was going on I came here as fast as I could. I was worried something might happen to you.
Tindoiimu: ...It's fine. I'm quitting the tournament.
Juan-Yun: What!? No! You can't!
Tindoiimu: It has nothing to do with you. I need to protect my people—
Juan-Yun: You have to stay in the tournament! That's the only reason they didn't kill you along with the others!
Juan-Yun: If you quit the tournament, there's no way you can protect yourself anymore, let alone your people!
Juan-Yun: Even Himawari can see that! Why don't you get it!?
Tindoiimu: ...I—
Juan-Yun: Uh oh, my spirit wind is starting to... fade...
Tindoiimu: Your face... don't force yourself!!
Juan-Yun: Guh... you caught me... I thought I was making this look so easy... mngh...
Juan-Yun: ...Agh... mngh...
Tindoiimu: What's the point!? Why do all this for me!?
Tindoiimu: Is it because of... Butter!?
Tindoiimu: If I die, you die too. Is that it...?
Tindoiimu: If that's the case, then give it back to me! We can end that stupid contract—
Juan-Yun: ...No...!!
Juan-Yun: This has... nothing to do with... Butter...
Juan-Yun: Even without butter...
Juan-Yun: ...Your fate... and mine...
Juan-Yun: Are already... intertwined... princess...
Tindoiimu: Juan-Yun!
Soohyeon: Juan-Yun, are you alright!?
Juan-Yun: I'm... fine... just need some... rest...
Himawari: ...Chiyuki! Can we get on with it, now!?
Himawari: Make it official, kick this maggot out of the tournament!
Chiyuki: Um... Princess Tindoiimu, do you still want to... resign?
Chiyuki: If you're certain, even though it's not following proper procedure, I can make your resignation official...
Tindoiimu: I—
Juan-Yun: No...! Princess... mgnh...!!
Tindoiimu: If you let my tribe be, then—
Insect POW: I don't want to live anymore! I want revenge!
Insect POW: Princess, you have to destroy the Udumbara! For us!!
Tindoiimu: No, stop!!
Tindoiimu: No... No... yaagh!!
Juan-Yun: Princess!!
Tindoiimu: Ah... ahh...!!
Tindoiimu: Yaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaahh!!!
Juan-Yun: ...Live on...
Juan-Yun: ...Even if it's only for revenge... I want you to live on...
Tindoiimu: Yaaaaaaaahh! Gyaaaaaaaagh!!!
Tindoiimu: Aaaahh!!!!!!
Juan-Yun: Live on...
Juan-Yun: I beg of you, princess...
Soohyeon: ...Tindoiimu...
Toyokuni: ...Look at her, her eyes... empty...
Toyokuni: Like a walking corpse...
Chiyuki: She must feel their pain... like she's dying with them.
Pang: There's nothing worse than utter sorrow... I've felt that way before.
Pang: An indescribable pain.
Himawari: Juan-Yun, don't worry about her!
Himawari: If you keep associating with criminals, everyone will start treating you like one, too!
Tindoiimu: ......
Juan-Yun: Himawari, listen to me...

Baa Baa: It's not me! I'm innocent, I swear!
Please, just listen to me!
Toyokuni: What's all that racket?
Alliance Soldier: Sir Toyokuni, this girl aided the insect princess in freeing the hostages! She's a conspirator!
Alliance Soldier: The second she realized things were going south, she ditched the princess and ran! Almost broke my ankle trying to catch her!
Baa Baa: Would you listen to me, I'm not helping her out at all!
Tindoiimu: ...This has nothing to do with her, Baa-Baa's just a merchant. We just hired her—
Baa Baa: I'm the one who reported her in the first place!
Tindoiimu: ......
Himawari: ...The heck is this girl talking about? I don't understand...
Alliance Soldier: Criminal scum! Stop spouting nonsense!
Alliance Soldier: I'm sorry for the disturbance, everyone. I'll bring her away—
Chiyuki: Ah, hold on.
Chiyuki: I think there's been a misunderstanding here.
Chiyuki: This is Baa-Baa, is it not? She's the one who told Arbiter Maeok of Tindoiimu's plan to free the hostages.
Tindoiimu: Baa-Baa... you told her!?
Baa Baa: Mm... Don't worry, princess. I got a good price for selling you out~
Tindoiimu: ......
Pang: Why? You're a demihuman... You have no reason to help the Alliance.
Baa Baa: What does that matter, eh?
Pang: Wha...
Baa Baa: The beasts aren't the only ones who oppress me. There's lousy humans and demihumans out there just the same.
Baa Baa: And I profit from it, I can be pretty lousy myself.
Baa Baa: Like I told the princess, there are good people and there are bad people out there.
Tindoiimu: ………
Baa Baa: So that's why I never understood you and that Nigel, and what you're all fighting for...
Baa Baa: Why care about some pipe-dream like Atlas when there's money to be made right here?
Baa Baa: You know I'll always pick the higher paying job.
Tindoiimu: ......
Baa Baa: Remember when we first met, princess?
Baa Baa: I told you if there's money to be made, you can always count on me~
Baa Baa: I was helping another client first, but you gave me the better deal.
Baa Baa: And now I've sussed out the better deal, again.
Tindoiimu: ...You're still the... same...
Tindoiimu: You only helped me because... I gave you the better price...
Baa Baa: Now you're gettin' it~!
Tindoiimu: ...Who did you sell me out to?
Tindoiimu: Who gave you... the better deal?
Baa Baa: Hehe~ They bought my silence, too, so I'm afraid I can't say~
Baa Baa: ...Unless you pay me more, of course. Then I'll tell you anything~
Tindoiimu: ......
Tindoiimu: ...Baa...Baa...
Tindoiimu: I'm going to... kill you. For the sake of my people!!
Baa Baa: Yaaah! Uh oh!!
Chiyuki: Call the doctor... No, just get her back to the guesthouse!!
Juan-Yun: Princess! Princess!! Wake up!
